This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) because it presents a privacy mechanism for releasing personal data. It could also belong to cs.DB (Databases) as it deals with data privacy. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves sampling techniques. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) as it satisfies differential privacy.
